According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Doorbell Market was valued at USD 1.6 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 1.7 billion in 2025 to USD 1.9 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 2.5% during the forecast period. The market is experiencing steady growth as consumers increasingly invest in smart home security solutions, connected devices, and home automation technologies. Rising urbanization, expanding residential construction, and growing awareness of home security are fueling demand for advanced smart doorbells equipped with video surveillance, motion detection, AI-powered facial recognition, and two-way communication features.
The transition from conventional doorbells to intelligent connected systems is transforming residential security worldwide. Smart doorbells now integrate seamlessly with mobile applications and voice assistants such as Amazon Alexa and Google Assistant, enabling homeowners to remotely monitor visitors, receive real-time notifications, and communicate from virtually anywhere. Continuous advancements in IoT connectivity, artificial intelligence, cloud storage, and wireless networking are further enhancing product functionality and user convenience.
